{
  "stem": "10829.2",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He just didn't-- he didn't have any life in him to-- why should I?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My kids, my wife is dead, and I don't have anything.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Why should I suffer?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he didn't want to partake in too much of it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So what we did for about two years, two and a half years, if not more, my zeyde and I used to go out and search.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "At night, we used to search for food.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "For example, we used to go out to the farms, and we would get eggs.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this lays in my mind real good.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We used to go steal eggs at the farms.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Europe, they used to have on top of the-- in the barn on top, in the hay, they used to store their eggs for-- for the winter time.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we used to take a little pinhole, make an egg, suck it out, and then put it in the little cup.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you can-- you don't need bigger than a pinhole, you can suck an egg out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we used to suck it out and then spit it back out in a cup, and we'd bring home a few eggs.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the summer and the fall, when you go to peel-- pick potatoes, for example, we would never pick more than one or two potatoes in one-- I don't know if you've ever seen in a garden, but potatoes grow in patches.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Sometimes they'll have 10, 12, or 6 potatoes on the one root.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we'd never take more than one or two potatoes out of one root, and never-- never from one-- from one [INAUDIBLE] to the next.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But you would skip rows and get around, so they wouldn't trace you.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
